<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1106,368,394]" box="[151,1106,368,394]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,1106,368,394]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,1106,368,394]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">
<taxonomicName authority="Curtiss, 1938" authorityName="Curtiss" authorityYear="1938" box="[151,472,368,394]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maoa">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,299,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">Turbo maoa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Curtiss" box="[306,472,368,394]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" refString="Curtiss, A. (1938) A Short Zoology of Tahiti in the Society Islands. [Published by the Author]. Printed by Guide Printing, Brooklyn, New York, xvi + 193 pp." type="book" year="1938">
Curtiss, 
<number box="[412,472,368,394]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1938.0">1938</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a possible synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gmelin, 1791" authorityName="Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" box="[765,1106,368,394]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="setosus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[765,932,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">Turbo setosus</emphasis>
Gmelin, 
<number box="[1047,1106,368,394]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1791.0">1791</number>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,438,1183]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,498,438,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">
Original description (p. 
<number box="[441,485,438,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="191.0">191</number>
).
</emphasis>
“The 
<taxonomicName box="[570,632,439,462]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maoa">
<emphasis box="[570,632,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">maóa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a large sort of sea-snail, common on the barrier reef, and much used for food by the Indians. They break off its shell with a hammer, pick it clean, separate it from its hard knob, and put it in hollow bamboo stalks, with 
<emphasis box="[526,594,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">taioro</emphasis>
sauce. It will keep in that way for several days. (
<emphasis box="[1156,1227,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">Taioro</emphasis>
sauce is the clean meat of a ripe coconut, grated fine, and seasoned with the juices squeezed from the heads of river shrimps.) Its shell is large and rounded, the spire, however, coming to a point. It is grayish-brown outside, white inside, and like mother-of-pearl under its outer covering. The opening is circle-shaped, and without teeth, and under the foot is a hard, round knob, like half a marble in shape, with which it closes the opening when it is inside. The outside of the outer lip of the opening it variegated with yellow and chestnut-color, and has elevated streaks, which, becoming less elevated, run on around the spire of the whole shell. The 
<taxonomicName box="[841,904,727,750]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maoa">
<emphasis box="[841,904,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">maóa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sometimes found on rocks close inshore, but more usually on the barrier-reef. (
<taxonomicName box="[530,666,762,787]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maoa">
<emphasis box="[530,666,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">Turbo maóa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (Near Tautira.))”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,438,1183]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,299,798,823]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">Identity.</emphasis>
The description of the operculum (hard, round knob, like half a marble) leaves no doubt that this is a species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[380,446,834,859]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[380,446,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">Turbo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Four 
<taxonomicName box="[520,586,834,859]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[520,586,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">Turbo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[688,1049,834,859]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="argyrostomus">
<emphasis box="[688,702,836,859]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[715,867,836,859]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">argyrostomus</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[990,1049,834,859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1059,1405,834,859]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis box="[1059,1223,836,859]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">T. marmoratus</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[1346,1405,834,859]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="petholatus">
<emphasis box="[1415,1428,836,859]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,268,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">petholatus</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[394,453,870,895]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gmelin, 1791" authorityName="Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" box="[514,790,870,895]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="setosus">
<emphasis box="[514,527,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[543,624,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">setosus</emphasis>
Gmelin, 
<number box="[732,790,871,895]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1791.0">1791</number>
</taxonomicName>
, have been recorded in the 
<collectingCountry box="[1105,1300,870,895]" name="French Polynesia" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">French Polynesia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Trondle" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" refString="Trondle, J. &amp; Boutet, M. (2009) Inventory of marine molluscs of French Polynesia. Atoll Research Bulletin, 570, i - ii, 1 - 87. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00775630.570.1" type="journal article" year="2009">
Tröndlé &amp; Boutet 
<number box="[232,293,907,931]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName box="[426,590,907,931]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis box="[426,439,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[453,590,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">marmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would not have been seen by Curtiss as it was only introduced to the region during the 
<number box="[284,342,942,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1960.0">1960</number>
s (
<bibRefCitation author="Yamaguchi" box="[371,572,942,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" refString="Yamaguchi, M. (1993) Green Snail. In: Wright, A. &amp; Hill, L. (Eds.), Nearshore Marine Resources of the South Pacific. Institute of Pacific Studies, Suva; Forum Fisheries Agency, Honiara; and International Centre for Ocean Development, Canada, pp. 497 - 511." type="book chapter" year="1993">
Yamaguchi 
<number box="[512,572,943,967]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The utility of this species for food was emphasized by Curtiss. 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="argyrostomus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">Turbo argyrostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[359,469,980,1003]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="setosus">
<emphasis box="[359,469,980,1003]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">T. setosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
happen to be the two species most commonly collected for food in the South Pacific (
<bibRefCitation author="Yamaguchi" box="[158,352,1014,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" refString="Yamaguchi, M. (1993) Green Snail. In: Wright, A. &amp; Hill, L. (Eds.), Nearshore Marine Resources of the South Pacific. Institute of Pacific Studies, Suva; Forum Fisheries Agency, Honiara; and International Centre for Ocean Development, Canada, pp. 497 - 511." type="book chapter" year="1993">
Yamaguchi 
<number box="[293,352,1015,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poutiers" box="[363,522,1014,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" refString="Poutiers, J. M. (1998) Gastropods. In: Carpenter, K. E. &amp; Niem, V. H. (Eds.), FAO Species Identification Guide for Fishery Purposes. The Living Marine Resources of the Western Central Pacific. Vol. 1. Seaweeds, Corals, Bivalves and Gastropods. Food and Agriculture Organization, Rome, pp. 364 - 686." type="book" year="1998">
Poutiers 
<number box="[462,522,1015,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but Curtiss’s description is insufficient to clearly determine which. Based on our interpretation of the description, 
<taxonomicName box="[528,666,1050,1075]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="maoa">
<emphasis box="[528,666,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">Turbo maoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more likely to be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="Gmelin, 1791" authorityName="Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" box="[1106,1431,1050,1075]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="setosus">
<emphasis box="[1106,1263,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">Turbo setosus</emphasis>
Gmelin, 
<number box="[1373,1431,1051,1075]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1791.0">1791</number>
</taxonomicName>
, which is distinctly more round in shape and fits better with Curtiss’s description of a large rounded shell with a pointed spire as the shells of 
<taxonomicName box="[472,651,1123,1147]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="argyrostomus">
<emphasis box="[472,485,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[499,651,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">argyrostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
normally have distinctly angular whorls. 
<taxonomicName authority="Gmelin, 1791" authorityName="Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" box="[1115,1431,1122,1147]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turbinidae" genus="Turbo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trochida" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="setosus">
<emphasis box="[1115,1269,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="398">Turbo setosus</emphasis>
Gmelin, 
<number box="[1373,1431,1123,1147]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1791.0">1791</number>
</taxonomicName>
, is a widely-distributed Indo-West Pacific species (
<bibRefCitation author="Poutiers" box="[711,872,1158,1183]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" refString="Poutiers, J. M. (1998) Gastropods. In: Carpenter, K. E. &amp; Niem, V. H. (Eds.), FAO Species Identification Guide for Fishery Purposes. The Living Marine Resources of the Western Central Pacific. Vol. 1. Seaweeds, Corals, Bivalves and Gastropods. Food and Agriculture Organization, Rome, pp. 364 - 686." type="book" year="1998">
Poutiers 
<number box="[812,872,1159,1183]" pageId="4" pageNumber="398" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
